They Are Comming x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is kind of a simple deck to play.  It uses heavy Twilight Denial to rob your opponant of the much needed Twilight.  Bid one or two every game, if you lose the bid and they play Green Dragon Inn Start Aragorn, if they play anything else start Gimli and Sam.  Pull Bill out first turn and Aragorn if Possible to have some strengh in your fellowship.  <br />
<br />
All you have to do is give them nothing to work with any they will have a clogged hand and your shadow side should be able to get them but if that dont happen you can bring out Boromir and Arwen with their wepons to kick some butt and run if you have to.<br />
<br />
I decided to play Moria to cycle through your deck quicker and get more Freep peoples cards to get everything set up.  Also, with all the Uruk-Hai counters out there I figured that it would catch some people by suprise.  All you have to do<br />
with the Shadow is get out as many minions as you can and get a Cave Troll and you should be in good shape.  <br />
<br />
The stairway should do some damage for a Balrog at site 5 to kill some companions.  Also you can stop a fellowship at site 8 and have a chance to run past them and go to site 9 for the win.  Also, for the Free Peoples use Galadrial to get out your site 3 to get the movement bonus and get out your site 7 to skip the archery to help your minions when they go though that site.<br />
<br />
Thats about it if I see any Problems with the deck I can use the deck edit to fix anything.  Thanks for reading. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
